HEADWORD: Tonometry
<hw>To*nom"e*try</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
measuring with a tonometer;</def> <specif>specifically</specif>
<fld>(Med.)</fld>, <def>measurement of tension, esp. the tension of the
eyeball.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

